# Ashed credentials — optional, never required for auth

**Ashed connection keys / JWTs are NOT part of any authentication or onboarding flow.** Do not gate member link, Discord user link, alliance invite accept, or guild registration on Ashed credentials unless the feature explicitly consumes Ashed API data.

## What auth flows use instead

| Flow | Proof | Storage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Web member onboarding (`/onboard`, member-link wizard) | In-game **name + UID** → Last War lookup + roster match | `hq_member_links`, `alliance_memberships` |
| Discord HQ account link (`/link`) | Discord OAuth via browser (`user_link` nonce) | `discord_hq_links` |
| Discord member link (`/link-commander`, `/link-last-war-profile`) | Same **name + UID** proof in guild's alliance | `discord_member_links` |
| Discord guild registration (`/link-alliance`) | Owner via **member link** (`callerIsAllianceOwner`) or platform maintainer | `discord_guild_alliances` |
| HQ web session | Email / OAuth → `hq_users` + session | Session cookie |

**Never** require `discord_hq_links` for a member to link their in-game commander on Discord. `/link-ashed` **does** require an HQ link first.

## When Ashed credentials ARE used (optional follow-up)

Ashed is an **optional upgrade** after identity is established. It enables:

- **Roster sync** and iframe tools on HQ web (connect flow)
- **Bot roster reads** via `alliance_ashed_credentials` (`/link-ashed`)
- **Video processing** (only when the user has the processing role)
- **Legacy owner proof** via Ashed owner JWT on `/link-ashed` (parallel to native owner member-link proof)

`/link-ashed` → `/discord/authorize` with `purpose=alliance_credentials` is the **only** Discord browser flow that accepts an Ashed connection key.

`/link` → `/discord/authorize` with `purpose=user_link` completes **Discord OAuth** to bind `discord_hq_links` — not name + UID, not an Ashed key.

## Implementation guardrails

- Do not add `verifyBase44Connection`, `parseConnectionInput`, or connection-key form fields to member link or onboarding paths.
- Do not return `errors.hqLinkRequired` before member-link or guild-registration handlers — those flows do not depend on `discord_hq_links`.
- `discord_hq_links` is required for `/link-ashed` and optional for commander link; it is established by `/link` (Discord OAuth), not by commander name+UID.
- Bot paths stay **read-only** on Ashed unless a future feature documents mutating calls with owner JWT + audit.

